narratives.question_text: Please rate and comment on the following aspects of your experience in this course or module regarding: Workload
comments: Nice to get practical experience writing press release, pitch letter, and marketing plan. Sometimes the reading was too much for the amount of time we had to discuss in class. (An exception is Invitation to the Party - I was thrilled to be required to read the entire book. Seriously. It will inform my work for the rest of my career.)

narratives.question_text: Please comment on all aspects of your experience in this course or module regarding: Organization.Comments:
comments: Good progression of topics. Nice to build upon our knowledge of what works for audiences and what doesn't.

narratives.question_text: Please comment on all aspects of your experience in this course or module regarding: the Instructor.Comments:
comments: Naomi knows her stuff, and brings a well-rounded perspective from her producing, presenting, international, and music experiences. I consider her an expert - a patient and open-minded one.

narratives.question_text: Please comment on: Visitors, if any
comments: Best visitors of any class this semester. She truly got the cream of the crop - the absolute best people at what they do. All were inspiring, had excellent examples from their careers, and fun.
Sessions given by guests from Capacity Interactive, and David Snead from NY Philharmonic were mostly helpful among all guest lectures.

narratives.question_text: Please comment on all aspects of your experience in this course or module regarding: Your Learning.Comments:

comments: Naomi is a lenient grader, which I am fine with, but even if she was satisfied with my work, I would have welcomed feedback on room for improvement that I'm sure was present in my work. I'm sure with her advanced knowledge, there is much for me to learn from her (despite having learned so much in her classes).
